{"TopicId":37070,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Naval Exploration Ship \u0026quot;Mercury Trail\u0026quot;","CreatedByName":"SirJodelstein","CreatedById":62251,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T20:54:08Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"SirJodelstein","CreatedById":62251,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-14T20:54:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EToday i made a boat in KSP that actually looks like a boat. This is my new aquatic exploration vehicle \u0022Mercury Trail\u0022:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img812.imageshack.us/img812/4870/x037.png\u0022 alt=\u0022x037.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img834.imageshack.us/img834/6663/sg6i.png\u0022 alt=\u0022sg6i.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img41.imageshack.us/img41/2771/ekfq.png\u0022 alt=\u0022ekfq.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E17 tons, 135 parts. Safe top speed around 17m/s, with enough fuel to drive for about 4 hours (about 240km range). Yes, most boats are slow \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESpecial Features: A monoprop tank that looks like a radar scanner, steering wheel made with a small decoupler, ladders to fetch up swimming Kerbals, and Torodial Tank life buoys.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI want to send this thing to Eve \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMods used: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E - \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/ksf-boat-propeller/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EBoat Propeller Mod\u003C/a\u003E. (using a rescaled version of the part)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E - \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/firespitter-propeller-plane-parts/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EFirespitter Pack\u003C/a\u003E for direct water launch\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E - \u003Ca href=\u0022http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/aviation-lights-v1-2/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAviation lights\u003C/a\u003E for the positional lights\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E - \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/showthread.php/25695-Sea-Sickness-Cure-walking-on-floating-vessels\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESea Sickness Cure\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/fjiu6w7qn2pfcji/Mercury%20Trail.craft\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECraft File\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-07-14T21:18:38Z\u0022 title=\u002207/14/2013 09:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 14, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by SirJodelstein\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}